msg: Netlify Dear Netlify friend October was a busy month for the Netlify and JAMstack communities We hosted the largest ever JAMstack Conf in San Francisco launched new and improved docs opened a private beta program for Netlify Build Plugins and published incredible new case studies with customers like Restaurant Brands International Nike and Longo s Deliver web projects 10x faster with the subject: Four things to know
msg: Netlify Hey there in this email we d like to introduce you to four powerful Netlify features 1 Functions This is one of the most powerful things for building fully functional serverless websites We call this feature Functions We have an amazing creative team Functions let developers run server side code without a dedicated server If you can write simple JavaScript or Go then you can build robust backend applications and APIs and do things such as Process payments build or connect to an API send transactional emails to users read from or write to a database and more The possibilities are endless Visit the Functions playground https functions netlify com utm_campaign Onboarding 2 0 utm_content Feature highlights utm_medium email_action utm_source customer io to learn more about Functions and all the ways to use them 2 Forms On Netlify you can handle web forms without servers API calls or third party scripts Here s how to do it Add a form to your site using HTML Add the attribute netlify to the tag That s it Netlify will automatically begin collecting form submissions If you were expecting something more complicated here s what else you can do with forms on Netlify See and manage all submissions in your Netlify dashboard Create multiple forms Forward submissions to any email address Send submission alerts via Slack Filter out spam or add a reCAPTCHA Trigger actions via Zapier or webhooks Handle submissions using AJAX To learn more see a walkthrough of the process https www netlify com blog 2017 09 19 form handling with the jamstack and netlify utm_campaign Onboarding 2 0 utm_content Feature highlights utm_medium email_action utm_source customer io or read the Forms documentation https www netlify com docs form handling utm_campaign Onboarding 2 0 utm_content Feature highlights utm_medium email_action utm_source customer io 3 Webhooks Call us crazy but as web developers we love shipping things What we don t love is all the work involved with web deployments Initiating builds waiting for builds to complete notifying others updating tickets and a bunch of other things we wish would just happen automatica wait a minute Netlify webhooks can help Use webhooks to improve continuous delivery spend more time developing great sites and avoid fussing with integrations and deployments Incoming webhooks notify our servers to do something Outgoing webhooks make another service do something when events happen with your sites If that sounds broad it s because there are so many things you can automate using webhooks such as subject: Automatic deployment of taggerhq failed.
msg: An automatic deployment for taggerhq failed The build failed with the message Your account has reached its concurrent builds limit Token from user taggerhq gmail com was used to interact with GitHub This account was matched as the GitHub committer You can also check that the user who connected the app or pipeline to GitHub still has access to the app and to the Github repository In this case reconnecting to GitHub will often fix the issue If you believe that this build failure was not due to an issue in your app please open a support ticket https help heroku com

msg: Understanding funnels and drop offs FullStory Funnel time Whether you re focused on converting new customers or nudging users to complete critical workflows if you can understand why people aren t completing a set of steps you can uncover opportunities to improve conversions or engagement Learn the why behind the numbers To create your first funnel use OmniSearch to build a new segment with more than one event filters Remember you can just start typing to see and select links buttons or events indexed by FullStory Next don t skip this step scroll down to your analytics dashboard to see your new funnel and learn the conversion rates Once you ve created your funnel you can Save the segment so you can revisit this funnel and see how it changes over time Duplicate the segment and make a copy of this funnel where users do not complete a critical step and Watch sessions related to the funnel to gain quick insights about where and why users are getting stuck BUILD YOUR FUNNEL https app spark empathy and break down silos but that can t happen if you keep it all to yourself Share FullStory with friends There are two easy ways to invite your crew https help fullstory com hc en us subject: Netlify Newsletter - December
msg: Netlify Dear Netlify friend It s been an amazing year for Netlify and our community thank you for being part of it We re going into 2020 more inspired than ever with our continued mission of empowering you to build launch and ship your biggest and best web projects to date Netlify Top 15 from 2019 Let s recap the biggest updates features and educational resources of 2019 outlined within this article https www netlify com blog 2019 12 19 top 15 from 2019 features resources and news on netlify and the jamstack utm_campaign Netlify Newsletter December 2019 utm_content Netlify Newsletter December 2019 utm_medium email_action utm_source customer io in the Community forums Matter Supply delivers Nike campaign in 4 weeks with Netlify Nike enlisted Portland based agency Matter Supply to build a highly scalable responsive campaign site featuring Colin Kaepernick on a super fast timeline Matter Supply picked Netlify and the JAMstack so they could focus on building the experiential aspects of Nike s project as opposed to managing databases worrying about load balancing or scaling servers Their choice paid off in a major way 200 000 hits per day 0 9 second contentful paint and a happy client all delivered by 2 developers in a matter of weeks See the results and watch the video from JAMstack Conf SF https www netlify com customers matter supply nike site utm_campaign Netlify Newsletter December 2019 utm_content Netlify Newsletter December 2019 utm_medium email_action utm_source customer io Introducing Scully Angular now has a Static Site Generator Netlify as a platform journey the team at HeroDevs has built the first Angular Static Site Generator and it can be deployed to Netlify Scully uses a node CLI application to run Angular schematics so you don t have to learn any new language or syntax Read more in the blog post https www netlify com blog 2019 12 16 introducing scully the angular static site generator utm_campaign Netlify Newsletter December 2019
